  <thing id="rahibernat" name="Hibernation" description="Akatas can enter a state of hibernation for an effectively infinite number of years. Akatas do not take damage from starvation. Should an akata go for 3 or more days without eating, it seeks out a place to hibernate and then surrounds itself with a layer of fibers that quickly hardens into a cocoon made of skymetal known as noqual. An akata remains in a state of hibernation until it senses another living creature within 10 feet or after it is exposed to extreme heat. An akata awakened from its noqual cocoon can claw its way out in 1d4 minutes." compset="RaceSpec">
