  <thing id="raTriVenom" name="Tri-Venom" description=" A xacarba&apos;s bite can afflict an opponent with one of three separate poisons. Upon damaging a creature, the demon chooses one of the following venoms to inflict upon its foe. The\nsave DCs are Constitution-based.\nAbraxas&apos;s Blood: Injury, Fortitude. Frequency  1/round for 2 rounds; 1d4 Dex and 1d4 Wis, If victim fails two saves subjected to  confusion for 10 minutes and requires a  Will save to resist; Cure 1 save \nSpells that neutralize poison cure this confusion effect.\nDemonic Bile: Injury, Fortitude. Frequency 1/ round  for 6 rounds; effect 1d4 Str an additional 1d6 Str vs Good characters ; Cure 1 Save. \nVile Disjunction: Injury, Fortitude. Frequency 1/ minute for 2 minutes The creature is affected by a targeted greater dispel magic effect as if cast by an 18th-level caster. Cure 1 Save\nNeturalize poison and similar spells have no effect upon this poison." compset="RaceSpec">
